Dashboard split (5/5): extract chat, library, hq, home — split complete

Finishes the per-feature module split. Behavior-preserving.

- panels/chat.js: message render + send (wires its own button/Enter on load;
  side-effect import, no exports).
- panels/library.js: documents list + compiled outputs + upload wiring.
- panels/hq.js: Author HQ aggregate + relative-time helper.
- panels/home.js: active-project cards + home stats / activity feed.
- main.js is now a 175-line app shell: imports + nav (switchPanel) + status
  (loadStatus/startPolling) + theme + init. switchPanel is exported (home +
  library navigate); projects.js's renderHomeProjects import repointed from
  the main shell to ./home.js (home now owns it).

Final structure: lib/{state,api,ui,format}.js + panels/{personas,idle-tasks,
insights,settings,projects,chat,library,hq,home}.js + main.js. main.js went
2677 -> 175 lines across the whole split.

Verified: build clean (token placeholder + the 3 window.* globals present,
every cross-module function defined exactly once); a cross-panel import audit
(no module calls an un-imported function); npm test green (29 unit + API +
smoke); tsc clean. Acceptance gate: Mercury visual click-through.
